  <div class="sub-label" style="padding-top:0">Rules</div>
  <div class="grid-2" style="gap:16px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <div class="card card-sm" style="border-radius:16px">
      <p style="font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--content-body-primary);margin-bottom:6px">Coral is brand, not a button</p>
      <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--content-body-secondary);line-height:1.5">Never style a primary CTA coral. Primary actions are Tire (contrast). Coral expresses the brand — accents, illustration, moments of warmth.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-sm" style="border-radius:16px">
      <p style="font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--content-body-primary);margin-bottom:6px">One calm accent per screen</p>
      <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--content-body-secondary);line-height:1.5">The accent fill is the blue-grey family. Pick one accent moment per view. Colour is punctuation — generous whitespace does the rest.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-sm" style="border-radius:16px">
      <p style="font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--content-body-primary);margin-bottom:6px">Tokens over primitives</p>
      <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--content-body-secondary);line-height:1.5">Build with semantic tokens, not raw hex. They carry light and dark for free and keep every surface consistent across the system.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-sm" style="border-radius:16px">
      <p style="font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--content-body-primary);margin-bottom:6px">Frost needs a blur</p>
      <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--content-body-secondary);line-height:1.5">Frost fills only read as glass with a backdrop blur and the frost stroke behind them. Never use a frost fill as a flat solid.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Coral accessibility rule (kept from previous page) -->
