    <p style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--supporting-brick);margin-bottom:4px">Coral accessibility rule</p>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--content-body-secondary);line-height:1.6">Coral <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:12px">#f26961</code> <strong>fails WCAG AA</strong> on white for small text. Use Brick <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:12px">#d04740</code> — the <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:12px">medium accessible</code> brand fill — for text links, icons below 24px, and small button labels. The React <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:12px">accent</code> variant does this automatically at <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:12px">small</code> size.</p>
